{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/mockservicereference"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/UIComponentsReference"],"anchor":"Reference","generated":true,"title":"Reference"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" tracks a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"current"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" entitlement snapshot the way the real service reflects RevenueCat’s state: "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" updates it and pushes it through the stream, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" return it. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/finish()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" tears the stream down, and the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/customerInfoError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/restoreError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" properties inject failures for testing error paths."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This mock differs from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" in SwiduxPaywall: that mock’s stream finishes after the initial yield, which is fine for static previews but cannot model purchase, refund, or family-share updates as a sequence. This mock keeps the stream live until you tear it down."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For preview and test patterns built on this type, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Library-target","type":"heading","text":"Library target"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Product: ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Import: ","type":"text"},{"code":"import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Types","type":"heading","text":"Types"},{"level":3,"anchor":"docSwiduxRevenueCatPaywalldocumentationSwiduxRevenueCatPaywallMockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"heading","text":"``doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService``"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public final class MockRevenueCatPaywallService: PaywallService, @unchecked Sendable {","    public init(isPro: Bool = false, hasPermanentLicense: Bool = false)","","    public var customerInfoError: Error?","    public var restoreError: Error?","","    public func customerInfo() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot","    public func customerInfoStream() -> AsyncStream<EntitlementSnapshot>","    public func restorePurchases() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot","","    public func send(_ snapshot: EntitlementSnapshot)","    public func finish()","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference type. Internal state is guarded by an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSLock"},{"type":"text","text":"; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@unchecked Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" because the protected mutable state lives behind that lock."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"Initializer","type":"heading","text":"Initializer"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public init(isPro: Bool = false, hasPermanentLicense: Bool = false)"]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"isPro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — Initial value for ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot.isPro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — Initial value for ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot.hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The values supplied here become the starting "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"current"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" snapshot — what "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" return and what "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfoStream()"},{"type":"text","text":" yields first, until "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" replaces it."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"customerInfoError--restoreError","type":"heading","text":"`customerInfoError` \/ `restoreError`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional errors thrown by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively while set ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", the default, means success). Set them to drive the plugin’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed"},{"type":"text","text":" path, retry affordances, or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ResilientPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":"’s last-known-good fallback; clear them to restore success."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"customerInfo-async-throws-%3E-EntitlementSnapshot","type":"heading","text":"`customerInfo() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the current snapshot — the init-time state, or the latest value passed to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". This matches the real service: the plugin’s dismiss-triggered refresh sees the same state the stream delivered, so a simulated purchase does not regress to free on refresh. Throws "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/customerInfoError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instead when it is set."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"customerInfoStream-%3E-AsyncStream%3CEntitlementSnapshot%3E","type":"heading","text":"`customerInfoStream() -> AsyncStream<EntitlementSnapshot>`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yields the current snapshot, then every value passed to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The stream stays open until "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/finish()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is called."}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each call to this method replaces the active continuation and finishes the previous stream, so an earlier subscriber’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"for await"},{"type":"text","text":" loop terminates instead of hanging. Only the most recent subscriber receives subsequent "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" updates."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"restorePurchases-async-throws-%3E-EntitlementSnapshot","type":"heading","text":"`restorePurchases() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the current snapshot, exactly like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":". Throws "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/restoreError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instead when it is set."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"docSwiduxRevenueCatPaywalldocumentationSwiduxRevenueCatPaywallMockRevenueCatPaywallServicesend","type":"heading","text":"``doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)``"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public func send(_ snapshot: EntitlementSnapshot)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes the snapshot current and pushes it to the active stream subscriber. If no stream is active, the snapshot is still recorded — only the stream delivery is skipped."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this to simulate purchase, expiration, or family-share updates during a test."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"docSwiduxRevenueCatPaywalldocumentationSwiduxRevenueCatPaywallMockRevenueCatPaywallServicefinish","type":"heading","text":"``doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/finish()``"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public func finish()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finishes the active entitlement stream. Iterators terminate cleanly. Subsequent calls to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" still update the current snapshot but are no longer delivered to a stream."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call this in test teardown or when a preview is done observing entitlement transitions."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Lifecycle-example","type":"heading","text":"Lifecycle example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let mock = MockRevenueCatPaywallService(isPro: false)","let stream = mock.customerInfoStream()","","var iterator = stream.makeAsyncIterator()","let initial = await iterator.next()  \/\/ EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: false, ...)","","mock.send(EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: true))","let updated = await iterator.next()  \/\/ EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: true, ...)","","mock.finish()","let terminal = await iterator.next()  \/\/ nil — stream finished","","let refreshed = try await mock.customerInfo()  \/\/ EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: true, ...) — send(_:) updated it"]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"role":"article","title":"Mock Service Reference","roleHeading":"Article"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"API reference for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" — a controllable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" conformer for previews and tests that does not touch "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/MockRevenueCatPaywallService/customerInfo()":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/mockrevenuecatpaywallservice\/customerinfo()","title":"customerInfo()","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/customerInfo()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"customerInfo","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() ","kind":"text"},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EntitlementSnapshot","preciseIdentifier":"s:13SwiduxPaywall19EntitlementSnapshotV","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the current snapshot — the init-time state, or the latest value passed to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService\/send(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/MockRevenueCatPaywallService/restoreError":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text"